        <h2>Project 1: Networking Design Project</h2>
        <p>This project involved designing a secure network architecture of a small company using packet tracer, linking 3 separate buildings together. It included implementing Vlans, creating subnets, usng different netowrking protocols, and testing connnectivity ensuring everything is fully functional.</p>
        
        <h2>Project 2: Networking Design Project</h2>
        <p>This project is similar to the last one, working in a group of students designing 4 separate sites of a medium sized company using packet tracer, using a variety of networking protocols such as BGP, IGRP, EGP, IS-IS, and OSPF. Setting up routers and switches ensuring everything is fully functional.</p>
        
        <h2>Project 3: Python Word-Guessing Game</h2>
        <p>This python project implements a word-guessing game where the player tries to guess a randomly selected word letter by letter, similar to "Hangman". The game has error handling for invalid inputs, such as non-numeric or out-of-range inputs. It also checks if the guessed letter has been guessed before. The program provides an option to exit the game during play. The players can choose to replay the game or exit after each round. This project offers an interactive word-guessing experience, making it a fun and educational game for players interested in word puzzles.</p>
        
        <h2>Project 4: Python Multi-Cipher Text Encryption</h2>
        <p>This python project implements a text encryption system that offers multiple encryption methods making it a versatile tool for securing text messages. It handles errors gracefully, providing default values when needed. The RSA Cipher generates a public key and saves it to a file for future use. The program provides clear instructions and options for the user to select the desired encryption method. The encription methods used are Caesar Cipher, Subsitution Cipher, Transposition Cipher, RSA Cipher(using RSA 1024 keys), Playfair Cipher, and the Product Cipher.
        </p>
